title: College football | Ohio roundup: Toledo has no problem with Eastern Michigan | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
No. 22 Toledo 63, Eastern Michigan 20: Phillip Ely threw for 327 yards and four touchdowns to lead host Toledo (6-0, 2-0 MAC) over Eastern Michigan (1-6, 0-3).
 
Northern Illinois 45, Miami 12: Joel Bouagnon ran for 134 yards and three touchdowns as Northern Illinois (4-3, 2-1) routed host Miami University (1-6, 0-3).
 
Bowling Green 59, Akron 10: Matt Johnson threw five touchdowns to lead host Bowling Green (5-2, 3-0 MAC) over Akron (3-4, 1-2). Pickerington Central grad Roger Lewis caught six passes for 118 yards and two touchdowns for the Falcons.
 
Kent State 15, Massachusetts 10: Shane Hynes kicked a pair of field goals, and visiting Kent State (3-4, 2-1 MAC) shut out Massachusetts (1-5, 0-2) in the second half.
 
Otterbein 28, Muskingum 21: Host Otterbein (4-2, 4-1 Ohio Athletic Conference) rallied from a 21-10 third-quarter deficit to beat Muskingum (0-6, 0-3).
Julian Lowe caught 11 passes for 92 yards and three touchdowns for the Cardinals.
 
Ohio Northern 52, Capital 31: After Jack Johns of Capital (2-4, 2-3 OAC) kicked a 39-yard field goal to tie the score at 31, host Ohio Northern (4-2, 3-2) scored 21 unanswered points to win going away.
The Crusaders totaled 530 yards, 500 on the ground.
 
Hiram 32, Ohio Wesleyan 31: Sam Conway kicked a 22-yard field goal with six seconds left as host Hiram (1-5, 1-4 North Coast Athletic Conference) rallied from a 31-20 fourth-quarter deficit to defeat Ohio Wesleyan (2-4, 2-3).
Quarterback Dominick Orsini and TraVon Wilkes each rushed for two TDs for the Battling Bishops.
 
Wittenberg 45, Denison 14: Zack Jenkins passed for 205 yards and four touchdowns, and host Wittenberg (4-2, 3-2 NCAC) stopped Denison (5-1, 4-1), which was held 227 yards.
 
Ferris State 38, Ohio Dominican 17: Ohio Dominican (4-3, 4-3 Great Lakes Intercollegiate Athletic Conference) was held to 45 yards rushing against host Ferris State (6-0, 6-0).
 
South Dakota State 38, Youngstown State 8: Taryn Christion passed for a touchdown and ran for another to help South Dakota State (5-1, 2-1 Missouri Valley Football Conference) beat host Youngstown State (3-3, 1-2).
 
Dayton 44, Valparaiso 14: Jack Adams ran for two short touchdowns in visiting Dayton’s (6-0, 3-0 Pioneer League) victory over Valparaiso (1-5, 1-3).
